  "prompt": "What do they call it when you get beat on a big play and you act injured in football?",
  "response": "In football, when a player pretends to be injured after being beaten on a big play, it is often referred to as \"playing hurt\" or \"faking an injury.\" Some people might also describe it as \"selling an injury\" or \"flopping,\" although \"flopping\" is more commonly used in other sports like basketball. Such actions can sometimes be viewed as gamesmanship, but they can also draw criticism for lacking sportsmanship.",
